genresAdvancedInfo.name: baltic black metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Baltic black metal is a subgenre of heavy metal originating from the Baltic states of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania. It is characterized by its dark, aggressive sound, featuring distorted guitars, blast beats, and harsh vocals. The lyrics often focus on themes of mythology, folklore, and anti-Christian sentiment.
